import math
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
% matplotlib inline
% config InlineBackend.figure_format='retina'

t  = np.arange(0,2.5,0.01)
y1 = np.sin(np.pi*t)
y2 = np.sin(np.pi*t + np.pi/4)
y3 = np.sin(np.pi*t - np.pi/4)

plt.plot(t,y1,'b-',
         t,y2,'g-.',
         t,y3,'r--')

  • matplotlib.dates
    MonthLocator DayLocator
  • DataFormatter

    xaxis set_major_locator( ) set_minor_locator( ) x

In [9]:
import matplotlib.dates as mdates

months = mdates.MonthLocator()
days = mdates.DayLocator()
timeFmt = mdates.DateFormatter('%Y-%m')
fig, ax = plt.subplots()
plt.plot(events,readings)
ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(months)
ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(timeFmt)
ax.xaxis.set_minor_locator(days)

    plt.text(x,-y,'%d'%y,ha='center',va='top')

In [33]:
dx = 0.01
dy = 0.01
x = np.arange(-2.0,2.0,dx)
y = np.arange(-2.0,2.0,dy)
X,Y = np.meshgrid(x,y)
def f(x,y):
    return (1-y**5+x**5)*np.exp(-x**2-y**2)
C = plt.contour(X,Y,f(X,Y),8,colors='k')
plt.contourf(X,Y,f(X,Y),8)
plt.clabel(C,inline=1,fontsize=10)

In [37]:
fig = plt.figure()
ax = Axes3D(fig)
X = np.arange(-2,2,0.1)
Y = np.arange(-2,2,0.1)
X,Y = np.meshgrid(X,Y)
def f(x,y):
    return (1-y**5+x**5)*np.exp(-x**2-y**2)
ax.plot_surface(X,Y,f(X,Y),rstride=1,cstride=1,color='#66ccff',edgecolor='navy')
